## üéØ Clinical Applications

### Primary Pattern & Manifestations
**Pattern**: Severe qi and blood deficiency with yang qi weakness
**Key Symptoms**: Profound fatigue, weakness, pale complexion, cold limbs, poor appetite, loose stools, shortness of breath, palpitations, dizziness, poor memory
**Tongue**: Pale and tender with white coating
**Pulse**: Deep, weak, and slow

### Secondary Applications
- Post-illness recovery and convalescence
- Chronic fatigue syndrome with severe weakness
- Cancer patients during and after treatment
- Age-related decline and frailty
- Post-surgical recovery
- Chronic anemia and weakness

### Modern Clinical Uses
- Cancer support during chemotherapy/radiation
- Post-surgical recovery and healing
- Chronic fatigue syndrome and exhaustion
- Immune deficiency and frequent infections
- Age-related weakness and cognitive decline
- Post-viral fatigue syndrome and long COVID

## üìù Therapeutic Actions
